1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:03,545
- [EMIL]<i> Liam Roja!</i>
- [GUNSHOTS]

2
00:00:03,628 --> 00:00:05,630
<i>Let's finish this once and for all!</i>

3
00:00:05,714 --> 00:00:07,799
- [CAR HONKS]
- [THUDS]

4
00:00:09,801 --> 00:00:11,177
[EMIL GROANS]

5
00:00:12,679 --> 00:00:14,597
[GUNSHOTS]

6
00:00:16,224 --> 00:00:18,476
[SCREAMS FURIOUSLY]

7
00:00:18,560 --> 00:00:19,811
[WHOOSHING, THUDS]

8
00:00:21,938 --> 00:00:24,190
[LIAM] <i>I ask all of you for forgiveness.</i>

9
00:00:24,274 --> 00:00:26,109
<i>For all that has happened to you</i>…

10
00:00:26,192 --> 00:00:27,569
<i>For all of the lives lost…</i>

11
00:00:28,069 --> 00:00:29,446
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

12
00:00:29,529 --> 00:00:31,740
<i>This place was never meant to die.</i>

13
00:00:31,823 --> 00:00:32,866
<i>I want to reopen it.</i>

14
00:00:32,949 --> 00:00:34,284
<i>It's not just a business.</i>

15
00:00:34,367 --> 00:00:35,702
<i>It's my parents' legacy.</i>

16
00:00:35,785 --> 00:00:37,370
<i>So I have to continue it.</i>

17
00:00:37,954 --> 00:00:39,622
<i>That was my promise to Papa.</i>

18
00:00:39,706 --> 00:00:42,917
<i>And I'm sure that's what Mama</i>
<i>would have wanted.</i>

19
00:00:43,001 --> 00:00:46,629
<i>But wait, who's going to</i>
<i>manage this place?</i>

20
00:00:46,713 --> 00:00:50,633
<i>"Olsen Bonifacio,</i>
<i>General Manager of La Playa Roja."</i>

21
00:00:50,717 --> 00:00:52,010
<i>It clicks. It clicks, dude.</i>

22
00:00:52,093 --> 00:00:54,054
<i>I know this is what you really want to do.</i>

23
00:00:54,137 --> 00:00:56,222
- [PHONE RINGING]
<i>- Mama keeps on calling me.</i>

24
00:00:56,306 --> 00:00:58,933
<i>She wants me to go with her somewhere.</i>
<i>I don't know where though.</i>

25
00:00:59,017 --> 00:01:03,063
<i>The ransom money has been returned</i>
<i>to the victims' families.</i>

26
00:01:03,146 --> 00:01:04,397
<i>But according to the report,</i>

27
00:01:04,481 --> 00:01:07,901
<i>they've yet to recover</i>
<i>jewelry worth millions</i>

28
00:01:07,984 --> 00:01:11,488
<i>that victim Ona Chan allegedly gave</i>
<i>to the hostage takers.</i>

29
00:01:11,571 --> 00:01:13,740
<i>Tell me where we're going first.</i>

30
00:01:13,823 --> 00:01:15,366
<i>To Magnus' rest house.</i>

31
00:01:15,450 --> 00:01:17,702
<i>But it's under investigation, Ma.</i>

32
00:01:17,786 --> 00:01:19,454
<i>We're going there?</i>

33
00:01:19,537 --> 00:01:21,414
<i>I just want to check something.</i>

34
00:01:21,915 --> 00:01:25,752
[GUARD] <i>I'm guessing that Homer Sebastian</i>
<i>knows where it's hidden.</i>

35
00:01:26,252 --> 00:01:27,504
<i>He's just not fessing up.</i>

36
00:01:27,587 --> 00:01:30,924
<i>But once he gets out of here,</i>

37
00:01:31,007 --> 00:01:34,052
<i>I bet he'll go back and get all of it.</i>

38
00:01:34,135 --> 00:01:35,595
<i>It's gonna be a feast for him!</i>

39
00:01:41,518 --> 00:01:43,186
- [KEY TURNING]
- [GATE CLANGING]

40
00:01:43,269 --> 00:01:44,521
[INMATE] Help him.

41
00:01:45,021 --> 00:01:47,148
- [INMATE 1] Hey, help him.
- [INMATE 2] Help him out.

42
00:01:47,232 --> 00:01:48,817
Carry him carefully.

43
00:01:50,151 --> 00:01:51,903
[INMATE 3] Take it easy. That's it.

44
00:01:52,779 --> 00:01:54,322
[GROANS]

45
00:01:54,405 --> 00:01:56,866
- [GATE CLOSES]
- There. Carry him carefully.

46
00:01:56,950 --> 00:01:59,994
- Assist him.
- Careful with him.

47
00:02:00,078 --> 00:02:01,913
- [HOMER GROANING]
- Be gentle.

48
00:02:05,125 --> 00:02:07,252
[GROANING]

49
00:02:07,335 --> 00:02:08,461
Homer.

50
00:02:09,295 --> 00:02:10,338
[INMATE 2] Homer.

51
00:02:12,006 --> 00:02:13,216
What?

52
00:02:15,093 --> 00:02:17,220
We heard that

53
00:02:18,263 --> 00:02:21,349
the jewelry you're hiding
is worth millions.

54
00:02:22,559 --> 00:02:25,103
Just tell us where you're hiding it.

55
00:02:25,186 --> 00:02:27,647
- Yeah.
- So someone can put it to use.

56
00:02:27,730 --> 00:02:30,400
We'll be getting out of here
in a few weeks.

57
00:02:30,483 --> 00:02:33,653
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

58
00:02:34,237 --> 00:02:35,738
Don't worry, bro.

59
00:02:35,822 --> 00:02:37,574
We'll split it with you.

60
00:02:42,328 --> 00:02:45,165
[GROANING]

61
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:48,334
[GROANS]

62
00:02:50,253 --> 00:02:52,130
You want to be rich?

63
00:02:52,213 --> 00:02:53,756
- Huh?
- [INMATE] Dude!

64
00:02:53,840 --> 00:02:55,884
- You want to be rich?
- Hell yeah.

65
00:02:56,593 --> 00:02:58,553
Find an island

66
00:02:59,137 --> 00:03:01,264
and take some hostages.

67
00:03:01,973 --> 00:03:03,683
This bastard!

68
00:03:03,766 --> 00:03:06,227
- Cocky, aren't you?!
- [CHOKING]

69
00:03:06,311 --> 00:03:07,437
Arrogant bastard.

70
00:03:08,313 --> 00:03:11,149
What're you gonna do
with the jewelry anyway, huh?

71
00:03:12,108 --> 00:03:14,152
You'll be rotting here
the rest of your life anyway!

72
00:03:14,235 --> 00:03:16,237
[COUGHING] I don't know anything!

73
00:03:16,321 --> 00:03:18,448
- You don't know anything?
- I don't know anything!

74
00:03:18,531 --> 00:03:22,619
- [BLOWS LANDING]
- [HOMER GROANS]

75
00:03:22,702 --> 00:03:23,786
What now, huh?!

76
00:03:23,870 --> 00:03:24,829
[HOMER YELPS]

77
00:03:24,913 --> 00:03:26,706
- I don't know anything!
- [KICK LANDS]

78
00:03:26,789 --> 00:03:28,166
[INMATE 1] You don't know anything?!

79
00:03:28,249 --> 00:03:30,376
- [KICKS LANDING]
- [HOMER GROANING]

80
00:03:30,460 --> 00:03:32,670
- I don't know.
- [INMATE 2] Let's see how tough you are.

81
00:03:32,754 --> 00:03:40,011
- [KICKS LANDING]
- [SCREAMING IN PAIN]

82
00:03:40,094 --> 00:03:42,430
[GROANING]

83
00:03:42,513 --> 00:03:44,140
- I told you, I don't--
- Kick him!

84
00:03:44,224 --> 00:03:46,434
- [KICK LANDS]
- [SCREAMS IN PAIN]

85
00:03:50,188 --> 00:03:55,568
[INMATE SNORING]

86
00:04:03,076 --> 00:04:09,624
[MENACING MUSIC PLAYING]

87
00:04:21,594 --> 00:04:26,683
[MENACING MUSIC CONTINUES]

88
00:04:44,242 --> 00:04:47,036
[INMATE SNORING]

89
00:04:47,120 --> 00:04:48,413
[PUFFS]

90
00:05:05,722 --> 00:05:06,597
[LIAM] <i>Let's go!</i>

91
00:05:11,686 --> 00:05:13,229
[VAN ENGINE STARTS]

92
00:05:14,981 --> 00:05:16,357
[SUSPENSEFUL STING]

93
00:05:16,441 --> 00:05:22,989
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

94
00:05:38,004 --> 00:05:44,260
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

95
00:06:04,113 --> 00:06:08,409
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

96
00:06:08,493 --> 00:06:15,291
[MENACING MUSIC PLAYING]

97
00:06:22,465 --> 00:06:23,508
[SUSPENSEFUL STING]

98
00:06:33,810 --> 00:06:40,525
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

99
00:07:09,679 --> 00:07:11,431
[LUNA] By the way,

100
00:07:12,014 --> 00:07:13,391
just so you know,

101
00:07:14,100 --> 00:07:16,894
once La Playa Roja opens again,

102
00:07:18,563 --> 00:07:20,440
I'll return to the island.

103
00:07:26,696 --> 00:07:27,697
[IVAN] Really?

104
00:07:28,906 --> 00:07:30,408
You can leave me?

105
00:07:31,534 --> 00:07:33,536
I mean, your sister?

106
00:07:33,619 --> 00:07:35,037
Shiela will be all right.

107
00:07:35,121 --> 00:07:36,330
Don't worry.

108
00:07:37,415 --> 00:07:40,209
She knows that everything I do
is for her sake.

109
00:07:40,293 --> 00:07:43,129
You'll relive your traumatic memories
on the island?

110
00:07:43,212 --> 00:07:45,047
There's nothing to relive.

111
00:07:47,467 --> 00:07:49,135
Because everything that happened…

112
00:07:51,387 --> 00:07:53,097
remains in here

113
00:07:54,223 --> 00:07:55,391
and here.

114
00:07:55,975 --> 00:07:58,478
Sometimes, I ask myself,

115
00:07:59,479 --> 00:08:01,439
why did it all happen?

116
00:08:02,648 --> 00:08:04,567
Because no matter how hard I try,

117
00:08:04,650 --> 00:08:06,652
I don't see anything good

118
00:08:07,403 --> 00:08:08,905
in everything that transpired.

119
00:08:08,988 --> 00:08:11,157
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

120
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:12,783
Except…

121
00:08:12,867 --> 00:08:14,577
We met each other.

122
00:08:14,660 --> 00:08:16,412
I didn't say that.

123
00:08:17,079 --> 00:08:18,789
What are you smiling for?

124
00:08:18,873 --> 00:08:20,500
I didn't say that!

125
00:08:20,583 --> 00:08:24,253
Luna, I think I'm in love with you.

126
00:08:24,337 --> 00:08:26,464
[ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYING]

127
00:08:26,547 --> 00:08:27,924
[GASPING]

128
00:08:28,591 --> 00:08:29,800
Seriously?

129
00:08:30,343 --> 00:08:32,386
[PLAYFULLY] Aw, why did you say it first?

130
00:08:32,470 --> 00:08:34,764
How annoying! [CLICKS TONGUE]

131
00:08:34,847 --> 00:08:36,933
Ugh, whatever. Me too.

132
00:08:37,016 --> 00:08:39,560
[CHUCKLING]

133
00:08:39,644 --> 00:08:42,647
[ROMANTIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

134
00:08:57,286 --> 00:09:00,081
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

135
00:09:00,164 --> 00:09:03,668
The police just won't leave
this place alone.

136
00:09:03,751 --> 00:09:05,127
I hope…

137
00:09:05,211 --> 00:09:07,672
- I hope they don't come today.
- [CAR DOOR CLOSES]

138
00:09:08,339 --> 00:09:09,757
What are we doing here?

139
00:09:09,840 --> 00:09:16,889
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

140
00:09:16,973 --> 00:09:18,558
[LIAM] Ma, what are you looking for?

141
00:09:18,641 --> 00:09:19,559
Hey!

142
00:09:19,642 --> 00:09:24,647
- [PANTING]
- [LEAVES RUSTLING]

143
00:09:27,191 --> 00:09:28,526
[WENDY SCOFFS]

144
00:09:28,609 --> 00:09:34,615
- [STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [LEAVES RUSTLING]

145
00:09:35,199 --> 00:09:36,701
- [OLSEN] What's that?
- [BAG THUDS]

146
00:09:38,869 --> 00:09:40,496
This is ours, son.

147
00:09:41,831 --> 00:09:43,040
[BAG THUDS]

148
00:09:43,791 --> 00:09:46,335
- [BAG THUDS]
- [WENDY PANTING]

149
00:09:48,129 --> 00:09:51,424
[OUT OF BREATH] I managed to get this
before the police arrived.

150
00:09:54,427 --> 00:09:56,137
What is it then?!

151
00:09:56,804 --> 00:10:00,182
[STIRRING WHIMSICAL MUSIC PLAYS]

152
00:10:00,766 --> 00:10:01,851
[WENDY] There.

153
00:10:02,435 --> 00:10:04,186
Ma, this isn't ours.

154
00:10:04,854 --> 00:10:06,022
What's going on?!

155
00:10:06,105 --> 00:10:07,690
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

156
00:10:07,773 --> 00:10:09,400
This is ours.

157
00:10:10,484 --> 00:10:12,194
[WENDY] This is payment for us!

158
00:10:13,154 --> 00:10:15,531
For me being imprisoned for ten years.

159
00:10:16,824 --> 00:10:19,327
For us being separated for ten years.

160
00:10:19,410 --> 00:10:21,579
For the death of your grandfather!

161
00:10:21,662 --> 00:10:25,041
What do you want? For us to suffer
for the rest of our lives?!

162
00:10:25,124 --> 00:10:27,835
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

163
00:10:27,918 --> 00:10:29,920
Olsen is right, Aunt Wendy.

164
00:10:31,339 --> 00:10:33,299
- You have no right to those.
- [WHISPERS] Ma!

165
00:10:35,176 --> 00:10:36,344
No.

166
00:10:37,553 --> 00:10:40,556
No one owns this money!

167
00:10:42,516 --> 00:10:43,851
Liam!

168
00:10:45,603 --> 00:10:48,356
You know what we've been through.

169
00:10:48,439 --> 00:10:49,774
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

170
00:10:49,857 --> 00:10:54,320
You know what I went through
for your mother.

171
00:10:55,529 --> 00:10:58,824
Who's to say that I have no right
to this money?

172
00:10:59,325 --> 00:11:00,326
Come on, Ma.

173
00:11:00,409 --> 00:11:01,911
- Ma!
- No!

174
00:11:02,912 --> 00:11:04,705
This is ours!

175
00:11:04,789 --> 00:11:07,458
Greta ruined our lives.

176
00:11:07,541 --> 00:11:09,835
We almost died!

177
00:11:10,836 --> 00:11:14,215
You've risked your life for them
countless times!

178
00:11:14,840 --> 00:11:17,301
And then what?
We're still going to suffer?!

179
00:11:17,385 --> 00:11:21,097
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

180
00:11:21,180 --> 00:11:22,973
I want nothing

181
00:11:23,057 --> 00:11:25,601
but to give you a good life.

182
00:11:25,684 --> 00:11:27,228
I didn't have the chance to do so

183
00:11:27,311 --> 00:11:29,855
because I was imprisoned
in his mother's place.

184
00:11:30,564 --> 00:11:32,024
[WENDY] It's right here!

185
00:11:32,650 --> 00:11:33,859
[CRYING] In front of us.

186
00:11:33,943 --> 00:11:35,736
Our life will finally be better!

187
00:11:35,820 --> 00:11:38,531
Will you please give me the chance
to do this for you?

188
00:11:38,614 --> 00:11:39,448
But, Ma…

189
00:11:39,532 --> 00:11:42,576
What do you want?
To work for the Rojas again?!

190
00:11:42,660 --> 00:11:46,122
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

191
00:11:46,205 --> 00:11:49,083
Are they the only ones
allowed to hog money?

192
00:11:49,166 --> 00:11:50,459
We're not?

193
00:11:50,543 --> 00:11:52,294
We have to remain poor?!

194
00:11:53,796 --> 00:11:55,339
Stay here at the bottom?!

195
00:11:55,423 --> 00:11:57,675
There is a lot you can do with money.

196
00:11:59,844 --> 00:12:02,012
Money can make your life better.

197
00:12:02,096 --> 00:12:04,515
Yeah. It's true.

198
00:12:04,598 --> 00:12:07,184
- [MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [WENDY SOBBING]

199
00:12:07,268 --> 00:12:10,438
But if I learned one thing
from all that has happened, it's this.

200
00:12:13,107 --> 00:12:15,818
Money and material possessions
are not the answer.

201
00:12:18,821 --> 00:12:20,781
A lot of people got hurt.

202
00:12:23,409 --> 00:12:24,702
Sacrificed.

203
00:12:25,327 --> 00:12:27,621
People died just because of money.

204
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:34,462
Mama thought that it was the solution
to keep our family together.

205
00:12:36,297 --> 00:12:37,506
[LIAM] She was wrong.

206
00:12:37,590 --> 00:12:39,258
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

207
00:12:39,341 --> 00:12:40,426
In the end,

208
00:12:41,343 --> 00:12:43,596
she paid for it with her life.

209
00:12:46,474 --> 00:12:47,516
Ma…

210
00:12:48,017 --> 00:12:49,560
Ma, money…

211
00:12:50,811 --> 00:12:52,104
If we lose it…

212
00:12:52,188 --> 00:12:54,398
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

213
00:12:54,482 --> 00:12:56,358
…we can still get it back.

214
00:12:57,693 --> 00:12:59,445
We can just earn it back.

215
00:13:00,196 --> 00:13:02,072
We can just start again.

216
00:13:02,156 --> 00:13:03,491
But…

217
00:13:05,951 --> 00:13:07,828
But when you lose someone…

218
00:13:11,248 --> 00:13:12,249
There's nothing.

219
00:13:12,333 --> 00:13:13,876
They'll never come back.

220
00:13:13,959 --> 00:13:15,753
Just like Grandpa Ben.

221
00:13:15,836 --> 00:13:16,795
Right?

222
00:13:16,879 --> 00:13:20,007
[SOBBING]

223
00:13:21,175 --> 00:13:22,885
What if it puts…

224
00:13:22,968 --> 00:13:24,762
Puts your life in danger?

225
00:13:25,387 --> 00:13:26,639
Hm?

226
00:13:27,932 --> 00:13:30,309
What if you get thrown back in jail

227
00:13:30,392 --> 00:13:31,560
just because of that?

228
00:13:31,644 --> 00:13:33,312
Ma, do you think I can handle it?

229
00:13:34,688 --> 00:13:36,732
Losing you again?

230
00:13:37,441 --> 00:13:41,445
- [SOBBING]
- Right?

231
00:13:42,988 --> 00:13:45,908
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

232
00:13:45,991 --> 00:13:47,117
Ma.

233
00:13:48,869 --> 00:13:52,623
Isn't what we have already
important to you?

234
00:13:53,332 --> 00:13:54,667
Us staying together.

235
00:13:55,834 --> 00:13:57,586
Living in peace.

236
00:14:00,089 --> 00:14:01,757
[LIAM] I'd give anything

237
00:14:03,342 --> 00:14:04,760
if it meant

238
00:14:06,011 --> 00:14:07,888
I could be with Mama again.

239
00:14:10,224 --> 00:14:11,976
For my family to be together again.

240
00:14:12,059 --> 00:14:13,143
[WENDY SNIFFLES]

241
00:14:14,645 --> 00:14:16,897
But we all know it's not gonna happen.

242
00:14:20,943 --> 00:14:22,528
So, Aunt Wendy…

243
00:14:24,989 --> 00:14:29,493
Don't let your family, your life,
or your reputation get ruined

244
00:14:30,494 --> 00:14:32,454
just because of that.

245
00:14:32,538 --> 00:14:35,082
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

246
00:14:35,165 --> 00:14:37,835
[OLSEN] Ma, I also want
our lives to be better.

247
00:14:38,627 --> 00:14:40,504
I already told you that.

248
00:14:41,839 --> 00:14:43,966
But in the right way.

249
00:14:46,260 --> 00:14:48,053
Earning it.

250
00:14:48,137 --> 00:14:49,597
Working for it.

251
00:14:50,723 --> 00:14:52,766
So we can be proud of it.

252
00:14:56,937 --> 00:14:58,814
After everything…

253
00:15:01,483 --> 00:15:03,444
my family is still wealthy.

254
00:15:05,404 --> 00:15:07,072
We have properties worth millions.

255
00:15:07,156 --> 00:15:09,158
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

256
00:15:09,241 --> 00:15:10,117
[SNIFFLES]

257
00:15:10,200 --> 00:15:12,036
But the question is,

258
00:15:13,704 --> 00:15:15,456
are Papa and I happy?

259
00:15:20,502 --> 00:15:22,713
Wealth doesn't make the world go round.

260
00:15:22,796 --> 00:15:25,883
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

261
00:15:25,966 --> 00:15:28,177
Principles are true wealth.

262
00:15:30,262 --> 00:15:32,598
Being there for each other.

263
00:15:34,975 --> 00:15:36,894
Doing the right thing.

264
00:15:37,811 --> 00:15:39,355
And choosing what's right,

265
00:15:40,022 --> 00:15:41,523
even if it hurts.

266
00:15:43,108 --> 00:15:44,610
For your family.

267
00:15:44,693 --> 00:15:49,239
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

268
00:15:49,323 --> 00:15:50,240
Ma.

269
00:15:50,324 --> 00:15:52,451
The decision is yours, Aunt Wendy.

270
00:15:56,747 --> 00:15:58,332
What choice will you make?

271
00:15:59,750 --> 00:16:01,418
[OLSEN EXHALES] Ma.

272
00:16:02,878 --> 00:16:04,546
You and Grandpa Ben

273
00:16:05,965 --> 00:16:08,425
taught me right from wrong.

274
00:16:13,097 --> 00:16:14,723
And I always keep that in mind.

275
00:16:16,058 --> 00:16:18,811
[SNIFFLES] If Grandpa were alive today…

276
00:16:20,020 --> 00:16:21,897
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

277
00:16:23,065 --> 00:16:24,942
…do you think he'd agree
with what you want?

278
00:16:27,069 --> 00:16:28,028
[OLSEN] No, right?

279
00:16:28,112 --> 00:16:34,535
[WENDY SOBBING, SNIFFLING]

280
00:16:34,618 --> 00:16:35,661
Let me have it.

281
00:16:36,245 --> 00:16:37,204
Ma…

282
00:16:37,788 --> 00:16:38,872
Let go of it.

283
00:16:40,290 --> 00:16:41,291
[SOFTLY] Let go of it.

284
00:16:41,375 --> 00:16:45,629
[SOBBING CONTINUES]

285
00:16:53,887 --> 00:16:56,598
We will never get that much-- [CRYING]

286
00:16:56,682 --> 00:16:58,017
Oh, son!

287
00:16:58,100 --> 00:16:59,435
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

288
00:16:59,518 --> 00:17:04,189
[CRYING CONTINUES]

289
00:17:21,498 --> 00:17:24,668
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

290
00:17:25,627 --> 00:17:26,795
[MUSIC FADES]

291
00:17:26,879 --> 00:17:29,673
- Are we going now?
- Not yet.

292
00:17:29,757 --> 00:17:31,592
The senator might be looking for you.

293
00:17:31,675 --> 00:17:33,719
No. I talked to Dad.

294
00:17:33,802 --> 00:17:35,262
I told him we were going out.

295
00:17:35,345 --> 00:17:38,557
It's my friend's birthday,
so do you want to go?

296
00:17:38,640 --> 00:17:39,933
Party?

297
00:17:40,017 --> 00:17:43,562
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

298
00:17:43,645 --> 00:17:44,605
I don't want to.

299
00:17:44,688 --> 00:17:45,773
Why?

300
00:17:46,482 --> 00:17:47,858
Macky,

301
00:17:47,941 --> 00:17:53,614
after all the things we've been through,
I've realized that life really is short.

302
00:17:55,282 --> 00:17:57,743
And I don't want to spend it
getting wasted,

303
00:17:57,826 --> 00:17:59,536
partying, and being intoxicated.

304
00:17:59,620 --> 00:18:01,038
I've saved some money.

305
00:18:03,582 --> 00:18:06,168
And I want to start a small business.

306
00:18:06,919 --> 00:18:08,670
Do you need an investor?

307
00:18:08,754 --> 00:18:10,214
Macky…

308
00:18:12,299 --> 00:18:13,592
I'm serious.

309
00:18:13,675 --> 00:18:15,511
Rita, me too.

310
00:18:20,516 --> 00:18:21,934
I'm invested in you.

311
00:18:22,017 --> 00:18:25,395
But didn't you tell me
you wanted to be a lawyer?

312
00:18:27,481 --> 00:18:29,358
You should make that dream happen.

313
00:18:29,441 --> 00:18:30,275
Rita…

314
00:18:32,486 --> 00:18:34,321
You're part of my dreams.

315
00:18:41,203 --> 00:18:42,079
Macky…

316
00:18:51,588 --> 00:18:54,550
[BOTH CHUCKLE SOFTLY]

317
00:18:56,593 --> 00:18:57,845
Macky!

318
00:18:57,928 --> 00:19:02,057
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

319
00:19:03,851 --> 00:19:05,102
[MUSIC FADES]

320
00:19:05,185 --> 00:19:09,022
- [WAVES CRASHING]
- [FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

321
00:19:10,023 --> 00:19:11,900
Babe, try this.

322
00:19:12,651 --> 00:19:18,115
[BRIGHT MUSIC PLAYING]

323
00:19:25,122 --> 00:19:26,331
Nice!

324
00:19:31,170 --> 00:19:32,171
[TONGUE CLICKS]

325
00:19:32,254 --> 00:19:33,505
[LUNA CHUCKLES]

326
00:19:33,589 --> 00:19:34,756
Get away from here!

327
00:19:34,840 --> 00:19:36,425
[OLSEN CHUCKLES, GUSHES]

328
00:19:36,508 --> 00:19:39,761
Get away from here! Olsen, cut it out!

329
00:19:39,845 --> 00:19:41,138
[OLSEN CHUCKLES]

330
00:19:45,058 --> 00:19:49,146
I'm serious.
I really love this, Chef Luna.

331
00:19:50,772 --> 00:19:51,773
Come here.

332
00:19:52,941 --> 00:19:54,610
Is that really the only thing you love?

333
00:19:59,531 --> 00:20:00,657
[GLASSES CLINK]

334
00:20:03,785 --> 00:20:05,495
I also love the one who made this.

335
00:20:08,665 --> 00:20:09,833
[LUNA GIGGLES]

336
00:20:11,585 --> 00:20:18,550
[MUSIC TURNS ROMANTIC]

337
00:20:19,968 --> 00:20:22,429
[BOTH CHUCKLE SOFTLY]

338
00:20:23,305 --> 00:20:25,182
[OLSEN] Mrs. Concepcion, how are you?

339
00:20:25,265 --> 00:20:27,684
Hi! It's our last day here.

340
00:20:27,768 --> 00:20:29,269
I hope you can visit again.

341
00:20:29,353 --> 00:20:31,855
- For sure. We will.
- All right.

342
00:20:31,939 --> 00:20:33,899
Thank you for taking care
of us, Mr. Bonifacio.

343
00:20:33,982 --> 00:20:34,900
Anytime, ma'am.

344
00:20:35,525 --> 00:20:36,443
Thank you.

345
00:20:36,526 --> 00:20:42,991
[LIGHT MUSIC PLAYING]

346
00:20:43,075 --> 00:20:49,331
[WAVES CRASHING]

347
00:20:57,005 --> 00:20:58,173
[TAPS LIGHTLY]

348
00:20:59,049 --> 00:21:05,430
["ROJA" THEME SONG PLAYING]

349
00:21:23,699 --> 00:21:27,202
["ROJA" CONTINUES]

350
00:21:35,127 --> 00:21:38,964
[FEMALE VOICE OVER]
<i>Welcome to La Playa Roja.</i>

351
00:21:40,299 --> 00:21:44,678
<i>There are places and there are</i>
<i>promises kept only for a few.</i>

352
00:21:44,761 --> 00:21:48,181
<i>Here, every journey is a bold adventure.</i>

353
00:21:48,265 --> 00:21:51,935
<i>Every arrival,</i>
<i>a story, waiting to unfold.</i>

354
00:21:52,936 --> 00:21:53,979
<i>Alicante Police Resort?</i>

355
00:21:54,062 --> 00:21:55,939
- [SILLY NOISE BLOOPS]
<i>- Argh! Sorry, sorry, sorry.</i>

356
00:21:56,023 --> 00:21:57,232
<i>Resort?</i>

357
00:21:58,108 --> 00:21:59,693
<i>- There's no more air!</i>
- [SILLY NOISE PLAYS]

358
00:22:00,777 --> 00:22:04,364
[FEMALE VOICE OVER] <i>La Playa Roja,</i>
<i>where opulence comes naturally.</i>

359
00:22:05,073 --> 00:22:09,286
<i>A grand banquet hall,</i>
<i>reserved for the rarest of tastes.</i>

360
00:22:09,369 --> 00:22:13,248
<i>Dinners with the best chefs</i>
<i>in the country.</i>

361
00:22:13,332 --> 00:22:18,045
<i>Because true luxury is knowing</i>
<i>you're always in good hands.</i>

362
00:22:18,128 --> 00:22:20,088
<i>Even when you don't see them.</i>

363
00:22:20,172 --> 00:22:22,215
- [SILLY BLOOPER NOISE PLAYING]
<i>- What are we going to do?</i>

364
00:22:22,299 --> 00:22:24,551
- [LAUGHS]
- [SILLY SOUNDS PLAYING]

365
00:22:25,427 --> 00:22:29,514
<i>Obviously… I mean, obviously,</i>
<i>they can see us on the CCTV.</i>

366
00:22:29,598 --> 00:22:34,519
["ROJA" THEME SONG
CONTINUES PLAYING]

367
00:22:34,603 --> 00:22:37,105
<i>You need to--Sorry. Argh.</i>

368
00:22:37,189 --> 00:22:38,815
[SILLY NOISES PLAYING]

369
00:22:38,899 --> 00:22:40,817
<i>I think I was half asleep for a while.</i>

370
00:22:40,901 --> 00:22:41,902
[LAUGHS]

371
00:22:41,985 --> 00:22:43,403
<i>Let's go to the private dock.</i>

372
00:22:43,487 --> 00:22:45,363
<i>I'll check if the cops really arrived.</i>

373
00:22:45,447 --> 00:22:47,074
- [SILLY SOUNDS PLAYING]
- [LAUGHS]

374
00:22:47,157 --> 00:22:51,078
[WOMAN VO] <i>Here at La Playa Roja,</i>
<i>your peace of mind is sacred.</i>

375
00:22:51,161 --> 00:22:53,246
<i>Your safety, absolute.</i>

376
00:22:53,330 --> 00:22:55,290
<i>What's the problem with Jacinto?</i>

377
00:22:55,373 --> 00:22:56,333
<i>Don't you know?</i>

378
00:22:57,417 --> 00:22:58,585
<i>- He's gay.</i>
<i>- Really?</i>

379
00:22:58,668 --> 00:23:00,253
<i>- Yeah!</i>
<i>- Really, huh?</i>

380
00:23:00,337 --> 00:23:02,172
<i>Get it, girl!</i>

381
00:23:02,255 --> 00:23:04,758
<i>- Oh my God!</i>
<i>- Let's go home!</i>

382
00:23:04,841 --> 00:23:09,930
["ROJA" CONTINUES]

383
00:23:12,516 --> 00:23:14,601
<i>I forgot my line!</i>
<i>What is it again?</i> [CHUCKLES]

384
00:23:14,684 --> 00:23:19,106
- [SILLY SOUND EFFECTS PLAYING]
- [ACTORS SOBBING]

385
00:23:20,190 --> 00:23:25,278
[FEMALE VOICE OVER]<i> La Playa Roja,</i>
<i>where every experience is unforgettable.</i>

386
00:23:26,363 --> 00:23:28,365
<i>Some you leave behind,</i>

387
00:23:28,448 --> 00:23:32,994
<i>and some you treasure</i>
<i>like a deep-buried secret.</i>

388
00:23:33,078 --> 00:23:34,579
- [JESSIE] <i>Hon.</i>
- [MAN]<i> Keep going!</i>

389
00:23:35,455 --> 00:23:36,706
[STAFF] <i>Stand by, action two!</i>

390
00:23:36,790 --> 00:23:39,251
- [SILLY SOUNDS PLAYING]
- [CHUCKLES] <i>You're silly.</i>

391
00:23:39,334 --> 00:23:41,169
- [CREW] <i>It's coming, it's coming.</i>
- [DIRECTOR]<i> Cut!</i>

392
00:23:41,253 --> 00:23:44,923
- [DIRECTOR] <i>Unfair. Cut, cut, cut.</i>
- [MAGNUS] <i>They're too fast!</i>

393
00:23:45,006 --> 00:23:48,635
<i>- They already passed the lamppost.</i>
<i>- They got us.</i>

394
00:23:53,890 --> 00:23:57,435
<i>That's Roberto Bobong Aguas,</i>
<i>Dado's recruit.</i>

395
00:23:58,937 --> 00:24:00,730
<i>- And that's Blacky.</i>
- [SILLY DINGING SOUND]

396
00:24:00,814 --> 00:24:01,648
[DOG BARKS]

397
00:24:01,731 --> 00:24:03,275
[EMIL] <i>Lucas Esteban.</i>

398
00:24:04,442 --> 00:24:06,319
<i>- Ex-special forces.</i>
- [SILLY SOUNDS PLAYING]

399
00:24:07,279 --> 00:24:09,656
[LAUGHTER]

400
00:24:19,916 --> 00:24:21,001
[DIRECTOR]<i> Cut!</i>

401
00:24:21,084 --> 00:24:23,378
<i>- You're dead.</i>
- [LAUGHTER]

402
00:24:23,461 --> 00:24:24,713
[CREW] <i>Oh, really?</i>

403
00:24:24,796 --> 00:24:27,757
[LAUGH TRACK PLAYING]

404
00:24:33,013 --> 00:24:34,556
- [DIRECTOR] <i>Action!</i>
- [GRUNTS]

405
00:24:34,639 --> 00:24:35,891
[CREW] <i>Attack.</i>

406
00:24:35,974 --> 00:24:37,601
- [OBJECTS THUD]
- [CREW] <i>Hey!</i>

407
00:24:38,310 --> 00:24:39,561
- [SILLY DOINKING SOUND]
- [GRUNTS]

408
00:24:39,644 --> 00:24:40,604
[CREW] <i>Okay.</i>

409
00:24:47,027 --> 00:24:48,236
<i>Team, listen up!</i>

410
00:24:48,320 --> 00:24:51,656
<i>The steak has to be</i>
<i>perfectly charred on the outside.</i>

411
00:24:51,740 --> 00:24:53,742
<i>Medium rare or rare.</i>

412
00:24:53,825 --> 00:24:55,702
<i>Gwen. Oh, Gwen, no. Sorry.</i>

413
00:24:55,785 --> 00:24:57,370
<i>I got the name wrong. Sorry, sorry.</i>

414
00:25:12,969 --> 00:25:16,264
[CHEERING, APPLAUDING]

415
00:25:16,348 --> 00:25:20,227
[SILLY SOUND EFFECTS PLAYING]

416
00:25:20,810 --> 00:25:22,771
[CHUCKLES]

417
00:25:22,854 --> 00:25:23,813
<i>Sorry.</i>

418
00:25:23,897 --> 00:25:26,942
["ROJA" THEME SONG
CONTINUES PLAYING]

419
00:25:31,488 --> 00:25:34,699
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

420
00:25:38,954 --> 00:25:42,040
<i>- Come on, come on, come on!</i>
- [CREW] <i>There are only a few of us.</i>

421
00:25:42,123 --> 00:25:43,875
<i>We're going home soon.</i>

422
00:25:44,459 --> 00:25:46,211
[FEMALE VOICE OVER]
<i>Welcome to paradise!</i>

423
00:25:46,294 --> 00:25:51,341
<i>We hope you have a wonderful stay</i>
<i>here at La Playa Roja!</i>

424
00:25:51,424 --> 00:25:55,178
<i>La Playa Roja,</i>
<i>the Crown Jewel of the South.</i>

425
00:25:56,179 --> 00:25:57,639
[MUSIC FADES]
